info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 03 at 2:31AM MDT until November 03 at 9:00AM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM MDT THIS MORNING... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County including Bordeaux along Interstate 25 between Cheyenne and Wheatland. Also, the South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills including Buford, Lone Tree and the Summit along Interstate 80 between Cheyenne and Rawlins. * WHEN...Until 9 AM MDT Friday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
